notesStmt.note: Reader's note dated 1239 AH [1823 CE] written in after the end of the text (f. 138r).

msContents.summary: Copy of a polemic by ʻĪsá ibn Muḥammad (al-Muʻaẓẓam), Sultan of the Ayyubid dynasty in Damascus against Tārīkh Baghdād by al-Khaṭīb al-Baghdādī.

respStmt.persName: ʻAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib ibn ʻAlī ibn ʻAlī ibn ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn, active 1226
علي بن ابي طالب بن علي بن علي بن علي بن الحسين،

supportDesc.extent: ii, 138, ii leaves : 204 x 146 (173 x 106) mm, bound to 204 x 137 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in clear naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

binding.p: Blue paper sides mottled with black over green leather with flap; paper labels on front cover and spine.

origin.p: Item is dated 623 AH and the scribe gives his name as ʻAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib ibn ʻAlī ibn ʻAlī ibn ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn (f. 138r).

history.provenance: Purchased for Columbia with funds from Alexander I. Cotheal.
